				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$J=\frac{9{\varepsilon }_{0}{\varepsilon }_{{{{{{\rm{r}}}}}}}\mu {({V}_{{{{{{\rm{appl}}}}}}}-{V}_{{{{{{\rm{bi}}}}}}}-{V}_{{{{{{\rm{s}}}}}}})}^{2}}{8{L}^{3}}$$\end{document}where ε0 is the permittivity of free space, εr is the relative permittivity of the material (assumed to be 3), μ is the hole mobility, L is the thickness of the film, Vappl is the applied voltage, Vbi is the built-in voltage (0.15 V) and Vs is the voltage drop from the substrate’s series resistance (Vs = IR, R was measured to be 10.8 Ω). From the plots of J1/2 vs. Vappl–Vbi–Vs, hole mobilities can be deduced.

